Shahbaz Ahmed bowling to K L Rahul, good length ball, pitching on off stump, K L Rahul opting for a sweep shot, mistimes it completely and the ball raps him on the pads . A vociferous appeal erupts from the Delhi camp, and the umpire raises his finger!
Rahul, however, isn't convinced. He wastes no time in reviewing the decision. The replays are tense, with everyone holding their breath. Thankfully for the in-form opener, Ultra-Edge provides a glimmer of hope. A faint spike is detected as the ball passes his gloves, indicating a crucial touch that saved him. The on-field decision is overturned, and Rahul lets out a sigh of relief as he strides back to the crease.
